# Paragnostic Initiate
Assist Casting			KEY:Paragnostic Initiate ~ Assist Casting			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Paragnostic Initiate Class Feature.SpecialQuality																																												DESC:You can assist an ally with spellcasting if you have a number of ranks in the appropriate Knowledge skill equal to the level of the spell being cast (minimum 1). The table below defines the required skills for each type of ally.	DESC:&nl;Ally Assisted Knowledge Skill	DESC:&nl;Arcane caster Knowledge (arcana)	DESC:&nl;Cleric or paladin Knowledge (religion)	DESC:&nl;Druid or ranger Knowledge (nature)	DESC:&nl;The type of assistance you can render varies with your level.	DESC:&nl;Penetration: Once per round as an immediate action, you can grant an adjacent allied spellcaster a +1 bonus on caster level checks made to overcome spell resistance.	DESC:&nl;Target: At 2nd level, you automatically aid any allied spellcasters in targeting a foe with which you are engaged in melee. Your ally does not take the standard -4 penalty for targeting that foe with a ranged attack spell, though the penalty remains in effect normally if other allies are engaged with that foe. In addition, you do not provide a cover bonus for that foe against any allied spellcasters. Furthermore, any foe you threaten takes a -1 penalty on Reflex saving throws against spells cast by your allies (but not by you).	DESC:&nl;Distraction: At 3rd level, you gain the ability to protect an allied spellcaster with whom you are flanking an opponent. As long as you maintain the flanking arrangement, your ally can cast spells without drawing attacks of opportunity from the flanked creature. Other activities that draw attacks of opportunity do so as normal.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.97
Tactical Combat			KEY:Paragnostic Initiate ~ Tactical Combat		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Paragnostic Initiate Class Feature.SpecialQuality																																												DESC:At each level you attain in this class, you gain an ability to enhance your fighting prowess or to influence magical effects cast upon you, based on your Knowledge skills. Each time you gain this feature, choose one of the following abilities for which you meet the skill-based prerequisites. Although you can choose some of these abilities multiple times (as indicated in the descriptions), you may not select the same one twice in a row, and the minimum required skill rank increases by 2 for each subsequent selection of the same ability.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.98
#
Avoid Energy			KEY:Tactical Combat ~ Avoid Energy				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Tactical Combat Class Feature.SpecialQuality										PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (the Planes)=4	PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (the Planes)=4																										DESC:Choose an energy type from among acid, cold, electricity, and fire. You gain a +2 bonus on all saving throws made against spells that deal damage of that energy type. You can select this ability multiple times, choosing a different energy type each time. (Knowledge [the planes] 4 ranks)																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.98
Break Point				KEY:Tactical Combat ~ Break Point				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Tactical Combat Class Feature.SpecialQuality										PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (architecture and engineering)=4	PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (architecture and engineering)=4																				DESC:Each of your melee attacks deals an extra 2 points of damage against inanimate objects and constructs. (Knowledge [architecture and engineering] 4 ranks)																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.98
Deadly Strike			KEY:Tactical Combat ~ Deadly Strike				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Tactical Combat Class Feature.SpecialQuality										PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Nature)=4	PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (nature)=4																										DESC:You gain a +2 bonus on attack rolls made to confirm critical hits. (Knowledge [nature] 4 ranks)																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.98
Discern Weakness			KEY:Tactical Combat ~ Discern Weakness			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Tactical Combat Class Feature.SpecialQuality										PRESKILL:1,TYPE.Knowledge=5																																	DESC:Choose one creature type from the ranger's favored enemy list (PH 47). Provided that you have at least 5 ranks in the appropriate Knowledge skill (Knowledge [arcana] for dragons, Knowledge [nature] for humanoids, and so forth), you gain a +2 bonus on attack rolls against creatures of that type. You can select this ability multiple times, choosing a different creature type each time. (Knowledge [varies] 5 ranks)																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.98
Mystical Augmentation		KEY:Tactical Combat ~ Mystical Augmentation		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Tactical Combat Class Feature.SpecialQuality										PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Religion)=4	PRESKILL:1,KnowleDge (Religion)=4																										DESC:Choose one clerical domain. The effective caster level of any spell in that domain cast upon you by someone else increases by 1, if you so choose at the time of casting. (Knowledge [religion] 4 ranks)																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.98
Physical Augmentation		KEY:Tactical Combat ~ Physical Augmentation		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Tactical Combat Class Feature.SpecialQuality										PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Nature)=6	PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Nature)=6																										DESC:Choose one of your physical ability scores (Strength, Dexterity, or Constitution). When any spell that applies a bonus or penalty to this score is cast upon you by someone else, any bonus granted increases by 2, and any penalty imposed is reduced by 2 (minimum penalty 1). You can select this ability multiple times, choosing a different ability score each time. (Knowledge [nature] 6 ranks)																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.98
Resist Ethos			KEY:Tactical Combat ~ Resist Ethos				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Tactical Combat Class Feature.SpecialQuality										PRESKILL:2,Knowledge (Religion)=5,Knowledge (the Planes)=5	PRESKILL:1,KnowleDge (Religion)=5,Knowledge (the Planes)=5																		DESC:You gain a +2 bonus on all saving throws against negative energy-based spells, and against spells with an alignment subtype opposed to one or both aspects of your own alignment (law/chaos or good/evil). (Knowledge [religion or the planes] 5)																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.98
Spell Disruptor			KEY:Tactical Combat ~ Spell Disruptor			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Tactical Combat Class Feature.SpecialQuality										PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Arcana)=6	PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Arcana)=6																										DESC:Any spellcaster flanked by you and an ally cannot cast defensively to avoid attacks of opportunity and is aware of this limitation. (Knowledge [arcana] 6)																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.98

# Sanctified One
Weapon and Armor Proficiency	KEY:Sanctified One ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Sanctified One Class Feature.SpecialQuality																																															DESC:If you are not already proficient with the chosen weapon of your deity, you gain that proficiency now. You gain no other armor or weapon proficiencies.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														AUTO:WEAPONPROF|DEITYWEAPONS																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.99
Spellcasting			KEY:Sanctified One ~ Spellcasting				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Sanctified One Class Feature.SpecialQuality																																															DESC:At 2nd and 4th level, you gain new spells per day and an increase in caster level (and spells known, if applicable) as if you had also gained a level in a spell casting class to which you belonged before adding the prestige class level. You do not, however, gain any other benefit a character of that class would have gained. If you had more than one spellcasting class before becoming a sanctified one, you must decide to which class to add each level for the purpose of determining spells per day, caster level, and spells known.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.100
# Cannot do without code support
Additional Class Skills		KEY:Sanctified One ~ Additional Class Skills		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Sanctified One Class Feature.SpecialQuality																																													DESC:Upon becoming a sanctified one, you gain the additional class skills specified for your deity in the accompanying table.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.100
Sanctified Ability		KEY:Sanctified One ~ Sanctified Ability			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Sanctified One Class Feature.SpecialQuality																														DEFINE:SanctifiedAbilityPool|0												DESC:At 1st, 3rd, and 5th level, you can choose a sanctified ability corresponding to your deity from the accompanying table. Sanctified abilities can be extraordinary, spell-like, or supernatural, as designated in their individual descriptions. If a sanctified ability is followed by an asterisk (*), you can select it as many times as you wish. Each time you choose it, the number of times per day that you can use that ability increases by one.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Sanctified One ~ Ehlonna|PREDEITY:1,Ehlonna	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Sanctified One ~ Kord|PREDEITY:1,Kord	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Sanctified One ~ Olidammara|PREDEITY:1,Olidammara	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Sanctified One ~ Wee Jas|PREDEITY:1,Wee Jas																																																																																																BONUS:VAR|SanctifiedAbilityPool|(SanctifiedOneLVL+1)/2											SOURCEPAGE:p.100
Sanctified Blessing		KEY:Sanctified One ~ Sanctified Blessing			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Sanctified One Class Feature.SpecialQuality																																															DESC:At 5th level, you receive a sanctified blessing based on your deity's powers and portfolio, as given on the accompanying table. Sanctified One Abilities The abilities to which you have access as a sanctified one are summarized on the accompanying table and described below, in the order they appear on the table.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Sanctified Blessing ~ Fast Healing|PREDEITY:1,Ehlonna	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Sanctified Blessing ~ Blessing of Kord|PREDEITY:1,Kord	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Sanctified Blessing ~ Fast Talk|PREDEITY:1,Olidammara	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Sanctified Blessing ~ Ruby Spell|PREDEITY:1,Wee Jas																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.100
